-- ==========================================================
-- BLOG DATA (INSERT OR UPDATE)
-- ==========================================================

insert into blogs (title, slug, excerpt, content, image)
values
  ('How to Choose the Right University in India: Complete Student Checklist', 'how-to-choose-the-right-university-in-india', 'A practical framework to compare UGC approvals, NAAC grades, fees, placements, and student support before admission.', 'Choosing the right university is one of the most important career decisions for any student. Before applying, shortlist institutions with clear UGC recognition, NAAC accreditation, transparent fee structure, and strong academic support.

Start with mode fit: online, distance, vocational, skill certification, or regular degree. Your preferred learning mode should match your schedule, budget, and career goal. Students who work full time usually prefer online and distance programs, while campus-focused learners may choose regular mode.

Next, compare outcomes. Look at program curriculum, specialization options, internship support, and placement guidance. Also review learning support such as LMS quality, mentorship access, doubt-solving process, and exam flexibility.

Finally, compare total cost of ownership. Check one-year fees, per-semester fees, exam fee, registration fee, and any hidden charges. A low fee is useful only if the academic quality and career outcomes are strong.', 'https://images.pexels.com/photos/1454360/pexels-photo-1454360.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1600'),
  ('Online vs Distance Education: Key Differences, Fees, and Career Value', 'online-vs-distance-education-key-differences', 'Understand how online education and distance education differ in class delivery, flexibility, fee model, and placement support.', 'Online education and distance education are often treated as the same, but they work differently. Online programs are technology-led with live classes, recorded lectures, online assessments, and frequent interaction with faculty.

Distance programs are more self-paced and document-driven. They are ideal for students who need maximum flexibility and can study independently. In many cases, distance mode is more budget-friendly, while online mode may offer better digital engagement and industry sessions.

When comparing online vs distance education, evaluate learning style first. If you need mentorship and structured schedules, online mode is usually better. If your priority is affordability and flexibility, distance mode can be a strong option.

For career growth, choose approved institutions and programs with practical curriculum, internship guidance, and project-based evaluation. Accreditation and university reputation are more important than marketing claims.', 'https://images.pexels.com/photos/159740/library-la-trobe-study-students-159740.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1600'),
  ('Top Career Courses in 2026: High-Demand Programs for Jobs and Growth', 'top-career-courses-in-2026-high-demand-programs', 'Explore high-demand courses in management, data science, AI, logistics, healthcare, media, and finance for better employability.', 'Course demand in 2026 is strongly influenced by digital transformation, automation, and sector specialization. Programs in management, data science, cybersecurity, logistics, healthcare administration, and financial analytics continue to show consistent demand.

For graduates, BBA, BCA, and BCom with domain specialization remain practical choices. For postgraduates, MBA, MCA, and MCom are still relevant when aligned to clear job roles like business analytics, marketing, HR, product operations, and digital finance.

Short-duration skill certification programs are also rising in value. Courses in digital marketing, UI/UX, data tools, and communication skills help improve interview readiness and role-specific capability.

The best strategy is to select a course based on your current profile, target industry, and salary progression path. Always compare curriculum depth, project exposure, and university support before admission.', 'https://images.pexels.com/photos/5212685/pexels-photo-5212685.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1600'),
  ('Best MBA Specializations in India: Marketing, Finance, HR, and Operations', 'best-mba-specializations-in-india', 'Compare top MBA specializations by career path, salary scope, and industry demand to pick the right postgraduate management program.', 'MBA is one of the most flexible postgraduate degrees, but specialization choice decides career direction. Marketing is ideal for brand, sales, growth, and digital roles. Finance suits valuation, banking, risk, and corporate finance careers.

HR specialization is strong for people management, talent strategy, and organizational development roles. Operations is best for supply chain, process excellence, manufacturing systems, and logistics functions.

Students should evaluate specialization through three factors: role fit, industry demand, and long-term growth. Avoid choosing only on trend; choose based on your strengths and work preference.

Before finalizing any MBA program, compare fee structure, faculty profile, curriculum relevance, and placement guidance. A specialization works best when the university provides practical projects and industry-linked training.', 'https://images.pexels.com/photos/3184465/pexels-photo-3184465.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1600'),
  ('Future of Data Science Careers in India: Skills, Roles, and Salary Trends', 'future-of-data-science-careers-in-india', 'A complete guide to data science career growth, required skills, entry-level roles, and salary trends in India.', 'Data science careers in India are expanding beyond IT companies into finance, healthcare, retail, logistics, and edtech. Employers now prioritize practical analytics skills, business understanding, and communication clarity.

Core skills include Python, SQL, statistics, visualization, machine learning basics, and dashboard storytelling. Entry-level opportunities include data analyst, BI analyst, reporting specialist, and junior ML support roles.

Students from BCA, BSc, BTech, MBA analytics, and even non-technical backgrounds can transition through structured certification and project-based learning.

For better outcomes, choose courses that include case studies, portfolio projects, and interview preparation. Recruiters value demonstrated problem-solving ability more than just certificates.', 'https://images.pexels.com/photos/669615/pexels-photo-669615.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1600'),
  ('Top Aviation Courses in India: Airport, Cabin Crew, and Ticketing Careers', 'top-aviation-courses-in-india-career-guide', 'Compare aviation programs like airport management, cabin crew, and ticketing with eligibility, duration, and career scope.', 'Aviation courses are becoming popular among students looking for service, operations, and travel industry careers. Common options include airport management, cabin crew training, air fare and ticketing, and airline travel support.

Airport ground operations roles require discipline, communication, and customer handling ability. Cabin crew-focused programs emphasize hospitality, grooming, safety protocols, and in-flight service training.

Before enrollment, compare course duration, practical exposure, language training, and placement support. Skill-focused aviation courses can offer faster entry into operational roles.

Students should also review total fees, certification credibility, and interview support to improve employability in airlines and airport service companies.', 'https://images.pexels.com/photos/358319/pexels-photo-358319.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1600'),
  ('Best Universities for Online Degrees: What to Check Before Admission', 'best-universities-for-online-degrees-india', 'Learn how to evaluate online universities by approvals, LMS quality, exam process, and student support systems.', 'Not all online degree programs offer the same quality. Students should check university approval status, NAAC grade, course structure, and exam process before applying.

A strong online university provides a stable LMS, live and recorded classes, faculty interaction, mentorship, and clear assignment timelines. Student support quality is a major differentiator in online education success.

Review university performance on transparency: fee breakup, refund policy, evaluation rules, and counseling support. Also check whether the program includes skill modules and industry interaction.

The right online degree is the one that fits your goal, budget, and schedule while maintaining strong academic credibility.', 'https://images.pexels.com/photos/267507/pexels-photo-267507.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1600'),
  ('Vocational Programs with High Employability: Diploma to BVoc Pathways', 'vocational-programs-with-high-employability', 'Understand vocational education pathways from Diploma to Advanced Diploma to BVoc with practical career outcomes.', 'Vocational education is a practical pathway for students who want job-ready skills. Many universities offer three progression levels: 1-year Diploma, 2-year Advanced Diploma, and 3-year Bachelor Vocational (BVoc).

This model helps students exit and re-enter learning with recognized qualification stages. It is especially useful for sectors like automobile, agriculture, hospitality, electrical, and healthcare support.

When comparing vocational programs, focus on workshop exposure, trainer quality, industry tools, and internship opportunities. Program design should align with real job roles, not only theory.

For students seeking early employability and skill-first careers, vocational mode offers one of the fastest and most practical routes.', 'https://images.pexels.com/photos/8199609/pexels-photo-8199609.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1600'),
  ('How to Compare Course Fees Smartly: Semester Cost, Yearly Cost, and ROI', 'how-to-compare-course-fees-smartly-and-roi', 'A clear method to compare total fees, per-year cost, and return on investment across universities and education modes.', 'Students often compare only headline tuition, but smart fee analysis requires full cost mapping. Always review one-year fees, per-semester fees, exam fee, registration fee, and any additional charges.

Compare cost against expected outcomes: curriculum quality, skill modules, internship support, and placement readiness. A lower fee is useful only if the course builds real employable capability.

For online and distance programs, check whether the fee includes LMS access, recorded lectures, and assessment support. For regular programs, include living and travel expenses in your budgeting model.

Use fee comparison along with course value and career pathway, not in isolation. This helps avoid low-value admissions and improves long-term ROI.', 'https://images.pexels.com/photos/4386370/pexels-photo-4386370.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1600'),
  ('Top Skill Certifications for Working Professionals in 2026', 'top-skill-certifications-for-working-professionals-2026', 'Best short-duration certification courses for professionals in digital marketing, analytics, management, and communication.', 'Working professionals increasingly choose short-duration skill certifications to upskill without pausing their career. High-value options include digital marketing, data tools, project coordination, financial analytics, and communication training.

The best certification is role-specific. If your target is growth marketing, choose performance and analytics-focused tracks. If your target is operations, prioritize process, reporting, and project tools.

A strong program should include practical assignments, live mentorship, and portfolio-ready outputs. Certifications with only theory have lower hiring impact.

Before enrolling, verify mode flexibility, assessment quality, and final project support. With the right course, professionals can improve promotion readiness and role mobility quickly.', 'https://images.pexels.com/photos/3183197/pexels-photo-3183197.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1600')
on conflict (slug) do update
set
  title = excluded.title,
  excerpt = excluded.excerpt,
  content = excluded.content,
  image = excluded.image;
